## Constraints
- Reuse existing helpers: `fetchTable`, `insertRow`, `updateRow`, `deleteRow`,
  `exportCSV`, `fmt`, `todayStr`, `monthsFrom`, `monthLabel`, `<MonthFilter>`,
  `<Modal>`, `<Field>`, `<SectionHeader>`, `<Empty>`.
- Navy/gold theme: `#1e3a5f`, gold `#e8b923`/`#c79a2e`, bg `#f4f6fa`,
  construction blue `#1c5fa8`, expense red `#c0392b`.
- snake_case columns; every table RLS-enabled with a policy.
- After schema changes: `notify pgrst, 'reload schema';` (full project restart
  if the cache misbehaves).
- Mobile-first (~380px). Test photo capture on an actual phone.
- One numbered step at a time; provide SQL for the owner to run; wait for
  confirmation before proceeding; `npm install && npm run build` clean before
  each commit.

## Done when
- Vendors managed by owner, readable by accountant.
- `receipts` bucket works: compressed upload + signed-URL display.
- Bills can be created with a photo, approved/rejected by owner only (DB-
  enforced), and rejected bills resubmitted.
- Clean build on production.

## Next (Phase 3)
Auto-post approved bills into `expenses` / `construction` via a DB trigger, so
the existing Reports stay correct automatically. Ask for Phase 3 once Phase 2
is verified.
